summary:
Having rattled through 6 episodes of Killing Eve today, I can 
categorically say that I’m at least 50% gayer, and I have become...
body:
Having rattled through 6 episodes of Killing Eve today, I can categorically say that I’m at least 50% gayer, and I have become so because of:

Sandra Oh’s hair

Jodie Comer’s face

And Fiona Shaw in power dresses and a fur hat

(why there isn’t a gif set of Fiona Shaw in that hat is a mystery to me)

Anyway - I’m 5% gayer having made this set, best stop before I start shooting rainbows out my eyes.

summary: Oh man I had been meaning to check out Killing Eve and two episodes in I am LOVING it, it's so weirdly... charming, for a show...
question: Oh man I had been meaning to check out Killing Eve and two episodes in I am LOVING it, it's so weirdly... charming, for a show with a whole lot of brutal murders?
answer:
Yes it is! Yes it is!! They skip so many of the usual strife plots in this kind of story, I think that contributes a lot to how fun it is to watch. Because while it has its own strifes, idk it’s just refreshing that it’s a different sort! And meanwhile at the base it’s just, assassins and moles and international espionage and all that comfortingly familiar stuff. Fun + Chill = Charming. Even with the murders.

theglintoftherail said: (Also I would like to put it on the record as of the end of ep 2 that I currently suspect the hell out of Big Important Russian Office Lady, I think she recruited Eve to keep an eye on her and is the person who leaked Eve’s name to Villanelle’s employers)

Fiona fucking Shaw is SO GOOD IN THIS that it would frankly be rude to her hilarious skills if you DIDN’T suspect there’s a lot more going on with this woman.
